quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  38,84,"God concluded, “The truth is—and I ˹only˺ say the truth—"
  38,85,"I will surely fill up Hell with you and whoever follows you from among them, all together.”"
  38,86,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “I do not ask you for any reward for this ˹Quran˺, nor do I pretend to be someone I am not"
  38,87,It is only a reminder to the whole world
  38,88,And you will certainly know its truth before long.”
  39,1,"The revelation of this Book is from God—the Almighty, All-Wise"
  39,2,"Indeed, We have sent down the Book to you ˹O Prophet˺ in truth, so worship God ˹alone˺, being sincerely devoted to Him"
  39,3,"Indeed, sincere devotion is due ˹only˺ to God. As for those who take other lords besides Him, ˹saying,˺ “We worship them only so they may bring us closer to God,” surely God will judge between all regarding what they differed about. God certainly does not guide whoever persists in lying and disbelief"
  39,4,"Had it been God’s Will to have offspring, He could have chosen whatever He willed of His creation. Glory be to Him! He is God—the One, the Supreme"
  39,5,"He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. He wraps the night around the day, and wraps the day around the night. And He has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term. He is truly the Almighty, Most Forgiving"